HEADWORD: Depasture
<hw>De*pas"ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To
pasture; to feed; to graze; also, to use for pasture.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cattle, to graze and <qex>departure</qex> in his grounds.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A right to cut wood upon or <qex>departure</qex> land.</q>
<rj><qau>Washburn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Depatriate</ent>⟦br⟧
